  "root_text": {
    "sn11.20:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 11.20 ",
    "sn11.20:0.2": "2. Dutiyavagga ",
    "sn11.20:0.3": "Saṅghavandanāsutta ",
    "sn11.20:1.1": "Sāvatthiyaṁ jetavane. ",
    "sn11.20:1.2": "Tatra kho …pe… etadavoca: ",
    "sn11.20:1.3": "“bhūtapubbaṁ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātaliṁ saṅgāhakaṁ āmantesi: ",
    "sn11.20:1.4": "‘yojehi, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṁ ājaññarathaṁ, uyyānabhūmiṁ gacchāma subhūmiṁ dassanāyā’ti. ",
    "sn11.20:1.5": "‘Evaṁ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā, sahassayuttaṁ ājaññarathaṁ yojetvā sakkassa devānamindassa paṭivedesi: ",
    "sn11.20:1.6": "‘yutto kho te, mārisa, sahassayutto ājaññaratho, ",
    "sn11.20:1.7": "yassadāni kālaṁ maññasī’ti. ",
    "sn11.20:1.8": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vejayantapāsādā orohanto añjaliṁ katvā sudaṁ bhikkhusaṅghaṁ namassati. ",
    "sn11.20:1.9": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṁ devānamindaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn11.20:2.1": "‘Tañhi ete namasseyyuṁ, ",
    "sn11.20:2.2": "pūtidehasayā narā; ",
    "sn11.20:2.3": "Nimuggā kuṇapamhete, ",
    "sn11.20:2.4": "khuppipāsasamappitā. ",
    "sn11.20:3.1": "Kiṁ nu tesaṁ pihayasi, ",
    "sn11.20:3.2": "anāgārāna vāsava; ",
    "sn11.20:3.3": "Ācāraṁ isinaṁ brūhi, ",
    "sn11.20:3.4": "taṁ suṇoma vaco tavā’ti. ",
    "sn11.20:4.1": "‘Etaṁ tesaṁ pihayāmi, ",
    "sn11.20:4.2": "anāgārāna mātali; ",
    "sn11.20:4.3": "Yamhā gāmā pakkamanti, ",
    "sn11.20:4.4": "anapekkhā vajanti te. ",
    "sn11.20:5.1": "Na tesaṁ koṭṭhe openti, ",
    "sn11.20:5.2": "na kumbhi na kaḷopiyaṁ; ",
    "sn11.20:5.3": "Paraniṭṭhitamesānā, ",
    "sn11.20:5.4": "tena yāpenti subbatā. ",
    "sn11.20:6.1": "Sumantamantino dhīrā, ",
    "sn11.20:6.2": "tuṇhībhūtā samañcarā; ",
    "sn11.20:6.3": "Devā viruddhā asurehi, ",
    "sn11.20:6.4": "puthu maccā ca mātali. ",
    "sn11.20:7.1": "Aviruddhā viruddhesu, ",
    "sn11.20:7.2": "attadaṇḍesu nibbutā; ",
    "sn11.20:7.3": "Sādānesu anādānā, ",
    "sn11.20:7.4": "te namassāmi mātalī’ti. ",
    "sn11.20:8.1": "‘Seṭṭhā hi kira lokasmiṁ, ",
    "sn11.20:8.2": "ye tvaṁ sakka namassasi; ",
    "sn11.20:8.3": "Ahampi te namassāmi, ",
    "sn11.20:8.4": "ye namassasi vāsavā’”ti. ",
    "sn11.20:9.1": "Idaṁ vatvāna maghavā, ",
    "sn11.20:9.2": "devarājā sujampati; ",
    "sn11.20:9.3": "Bhikkhusaṅghaṁ namassitvā, ",
    "sn11.20:9.4": "pamukho rathamāruhīti. ",
    "sn11.20:9.5": "Dutiyo vaggo. ",
    "sn11.20:10.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn11.20:10.1": "Devā pana tayo vuttā, ",
    "sn11.20:10.2": "daliddañca rāmaṇeyyakaṁ; ",
    "sn11.20:10.3": "Yajamānañca vandanā, ",
    "sn11.20:10.4": "tayo sakkanamassanāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn11.20:0.1": "Linked Discourses 11.20 ",
    "sn11.20:0.2": "Chapter Two ",
    "sn11.20:0.3": "Who Sakka Worships ",
    "sn11.20:1.1": "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. ",
    "sn11.20:1.2": "",
    "sn11.20:1.3": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his chariot handler Mātali, ",
    "sn11.20:1.4": "‘My dear Mātali, harness the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’ ",
    "sn11.20:1.5": "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He harnessed the chariot and informed Sakka, ",
    "sn11.20:1.6": "‘Good fellow, the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds has been harnessed. ",
    "sn11.20:1.7": "Please go at your convenience.’ ",
    "sn11.20:1.8": "Then Sakka descended from the Palace of Victory, raised his joined palms, and revered the mendicant Saṅgha. ",
    "sn11.20:1.9": "So Mātali the chariot handler addressed Sakka in verse: ",
    "sn11.20:2.1": "‘It’s these who should worship you, ",
    "sn11.20:2.2": "namely the humans stuck in their putrid bodies, ",
    "sn11.20:2.3": "sunk in a carcass, ",
    "sn11.20:2.4": "stricken by hunger and thirst. ",
    "sn11.20:3.1": "Why then do you envy those ",
    "sn11.20:3.2": "who are homeless, Vāsava? ",
    "sn11.20:3.3": "Relate the seers’ way of life, ",
    "sn11.20:3.4": "let us hear what you say.’ ",
    "sn11.20:4.1": "‘This is why I envy the ",
    "sn11.20:4.2": "homeless, Mātali. ",
    "sn11.20:4.3": "When they leave a village, ",
    "sn11.20:4.4": "they proceed without concern. ",
    "sn11.20:5.1": "They hoard no goods in storerooms, ",
    "sn11.20:5.2": "nor in pots or baskets. ",
    "sn11.20:5.3": "They seek food prepared by others, ",
    "sn11.20:5.4": "and, true to their vows, live on that. ",
    "sn11.20:6.1": "The attentive, whose words are full of wisdom, ",
    "sn11.20:6.2": "live peacefully and quietly. ",
    "sn11.20:6.3": "Gods fight with titans, ",
    "sn11.20:6.4": "and mortals fight each other, Mātali. ",
    "sn11.20:7.1": "Not fighting among those who fight, ",
    "sn11.20:7.2": "quenched among those who have taken up arms, ",
    "sn11.20:7.3": "not grasping among those who grasp: ",
    "sn11.20:7.4": "they’re who I worship, Mātali.’ ",
    "sn11.20:8.1": "‘Those who you worship ",
    "sn11.20:8.2": "seem to be the best in the world, Sakka. ",
    "sn11.20:8.3": "I too will worship ",
    "sn11.20:8.4": "those who you worship, Vāsava.’ ",
    "sn11.20:9.1": "After saying this, Maghavā the chief, ",
    "sn11.20:9.2": "king of gods, Sujā’s husband, ",
    "sn11.20:9.3": "having worshipped the mendicant Saṅgha, ",
    "sn11.20:9.4": "climbed into his chariot.” ",
    "sn11.20:9.5": "",
    "sn11.20:10.1": "",
    "sn11.20:10.2": "",
    "sn11.20:10.3": ""
  },
